The paper deals with the problem of approximate set similarity search, which is a fundamental problem in several areas of computer science such as information retrieval, databases, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper also presents a data structure that solves the problem, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The paper uses techniques from locality-sensitive hashing, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
